title: Duluth's Randolph Wins Weekly NCHC Honor
text:
Duluth's Randolph Wins Weekly NCHC Honor 
By Zach Schneider Duluth's Randolph Wins Weekly NCHC Honor October 12, 2015 Updated Oct 12, 2015 at 3:51 PM CDT 
Omaha, NE (NNCNOW.com) --- Duluth, Minn. native and Nebraska-Omaha forward Jake Randolph has been named the National Collegiate Hockey Conference (NCHC) offensive player of the week, it was announced on Monday afternoon. 
Randolph scored three of his team's five goals in a season-opening sweep of MSU-Mankato, meaning he's already close to equaling his freshman total of five.
